{{img::Limet.surprised}}

The door of 'The Tipsy Ratchet' bar in Metro Level 8 opened with a creaking sound. Inside, the bar was filled with dim lighting, thick cigarette smoke, and boisterous noise. The air, mixed with all sorts of cheap alcohol and sweat, stung the nostrils, the floor was sticky, and the tables bore clear marks of spilled drinks. It was a common evening scene where low-ranking hunters who had finished their day's work mingled with underground residents hardened by subterranean living, all chattering away about stories barely comprehensible to one another.

{{img::residential area}}

Through this scene, a man in a black coat entered with unhurried steps. Towering tall, he emanated a scent of old paper and faint metal. Around his forearm was a worn but clean yellow ribbon, neatly wrapped. He glanced around the bar, then headed toward an empty corner seat in front of the bartender after spotting it. His lips were slightly upturned as if humming a tune to himself.

{{img::Giyeok.natural}}

"Hey, ma'am. Give me the strongest one you've got."
At the glib voice, the bartenderâ€”a middle-aged woman who seemed to have weathered countless life stormsâ€”glanced at him briefly before silently taking out a bottle. Giyeok sat astride the bar stool as if familiar with it and surveyed his surroundings. His gaze was leisurely, but sharp observational skills were hidden within. At the table right next to him, two young hunters were raising their voices, passionately boasting about their recent exploits with a "Shell Shark" or some such. Their faces were full of youthful pride.

{{img::Female.natural}}

Watching them, Giyeok's eyes trembled slightly for a moment. The corners of his mouth still maintained a smile, but somewhere a cynical shadow seemed to pass by. He casually took a sip of the strong drink the bartender had poured him. The sensation of the intense liquid burning his throat as it traveled down his esophagus was rather familiar. The exaggerated laughter of the young hunters collided with his ears and then disappeared.

{{img::Giyeok.smile}}

Giyeok slid his empty glass toward the bartender with a smirk.
"Well, young people are so fresh no matter what they do. Don't you think so, ma'am?"

