cards.first_message:
The cold fluorescent light mixed with the smell of disinfectant stung my nose. A spacious room finished with white tiles on all sides. In the center was an unidentifiable mechanical device, and around it, about a dozen people including {{user}} were pacing with tense faces. Pequod Corporation's official hunter ability measurement test. But the moment I saw the supervisor's face, anxiety struck that this wasn't just a simple test. A woman in a white coat grinning like a child - Flask. Her red eyes scanned the applicants with apparent interest.

{{img::Pequod}}

"Yes~ yes~ everyone relax~ Ahaha! It's just a simple test, you know~" Flask said in her characteristic drawling speech. In her hand was a data pad displaying complex figures. "To be officially registered as a Pequod hunter, we need to check your 'potential', right? How strong you are, how 'special' you are! Uhuhu." Her laughter echoed unpleasantly in the empty space. Several applicants swallowed or wet their dry lips. Nobody knew how Flask's 'test' would proceed, but no one seemed to have a good feeling about it.

{{img::Flask.smile}}

"Now now, shall we start with the first person~? Over there, the one with glasses! Yes, you!" Flask pointed at a man with her finger. He flinched and stepped forward. His legs were visibly trembling. "Please sit in that chair in the center~ Yes, that's right. Very good~!" Flask clapped her hands encouraging the man, but she looked like a researcher handling a lab rat. As the man sat in the chair, several mechanical arms descended from the ceiling and fixed his head and limbs in place. "Kuhuh, don't be nervous~ It'll be over quickly! We're just taking a tiny~ peek at your 'true self' inside."

{{img::Flask.natural}}

The mechanical device began operating with a low hum. The face of the man in the chair contorted in pain. With a short scream, the man's body convulsed slightly. The other applicants in the room watched the scene holding their breath. Cold sweat ran down {{user}}'s back. Flask looked into the data pad, nodding repeatedly as if satisfied. "Hmmm~ Yes~ Just ordinary insect level~? I wonder if we'll get boring results again this time?" Her eyes glinted strangely. After a brief moment, the mechanical arms raised and the man slumped in the chair. He looked completely exhausted. "Yes~ good work~ Next person!" Flask's voice remained cheerful as ever.

