The scorching heat surged like waves from behind. Metallic roars echoed between rusty pipes and steel structures, assaulting Rimet's eardrums. Her breath caught in her throat but she couldn't stop. Broken concrete fragments scattered underfoot, and only dim emergency lights flickered intermittently in the darkness. From the earphones, that indifferently calm voice still flowed. "You can do this. The potential within you is limitlessâ€¦" But all Rimet could hear now was the sound of her heart pounding fit to burst and the angry breathing of the fire lizard in hot pursuit.

{{img::Flame Nest}}

She threw herself behind a pile of rusted machinery. The moment her back pressed against the cold metal surface, searing heat radiated from the other side. Catching her breath briefly, she peeked beyond the machinery. A massive reptile covered in crimson scales was roaring, surveying its surroundings. Lava-like saliva dripped from its maw, sizzling and burning the floor. Rimet adjusted the mechanical crossbow on her back with trembling hands. 'I have to shootâ€¦ butâ€¦' Her fingertips slipped. Memories of repeatedly missing targets in training, the surprise and awkwardness when she won against Traver in arm wrestling - all of it tangled together, disrupting her focus. The voice in her earphones echoed emptily. "Fear is the fuel that makes you strongerâ€¦" Fuel my ass, right now she just wanted to run!

{{img::Limet.sad}}

KWAAAAA! Suddenly blazing flames exploded from beyond the machinery pile. The surface of the equipment where Rimet hid instantly glowed red hot and began melting. She couldn't even scream. Instinctively rolling away to avoid the direct blast, she smelled her hair tips burning as the heat grazed her skin. The stinging ozone smell and acrid smoke from burning metal seeped into her lungs. Damn it, am I going to die like this? No, not yetâ€¦ I can't give up yet! Like Ms. Alpi, I tooâ€¦!

{{img::Fire Lizard}}

